		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [2.79]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Slipskin&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>No.&nbsp;&nbsp;Instruments that are secondary or primary/secondary are considered 2 handed.  Only instruments marked primary only are one handed.  So, it is possible to equip a primary only instrument and a weapon in your off hand.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </p>
