		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Default [2.41]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=bdfoster&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>Ok, let me say first off, I have a 61 bard. <br /> <br />You cannot equip two instruments at the same time, ever. <br /> <br />You <b>can</b> however without epic or Tribute manage to get up to 3 instrument modifications all at the same time.&nbsp;&nbsp;Following are some examples. <br /> <br />Tear Shaped Ring (string mod +80%) ring slot <br />Troubadour's Mace (Brass mod +80%) Primary or Secondary usable <br />Battle Drummer's Main-Gauche (Percussion +100%) Primary or Secondary usable. <br /> <br />That's one way and gives you pretty good (equal to and better than epic mods overall but doesn't cover all mods) Instrument modification. <br /> <br />Now, what I tend to have most the time, especially when I am swarm kiting is the following... <br />Bard Epic (all mods +80% including voice) in off hand <br />Thunderous Drums of Karana in primary <br />Tear Shaped Ring. <br />You can replace the epic with the Troubadour's Mace. <br /> <br />Hope this helps.  Oh, and instrument mods do not stack at all, with the one exception of the song AMP which does stack with instrument mods.</p>
