<p><blockquote><b class="sm">Quote:</b><hr size="1" />No.&nbsp;&nbsp;Instruments that are secondary or primary/secondary are considered 2 handed. Only instruments marked primary only are one handed. So, it is possible to equip a primary only instrument and a weapon in your off hand.<hr size="1" /></blockquote> <br />This is incorrect.  Any instrument that is Primary/Secondary equipable is able to have another item (non instrument) in the off hand when equiped in Primary. <br /><blockquote><b class="sm">Quote:</b><hr size="1" />There is only one way of having two instruments equipped at the same time and that is to have:  <br /><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=15738" title="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=15738" target="akztarg">http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=15738</a>  <br />Hope this helps, otherwise Slipskin is correct.<hr size="1" /></blockquote> <br />Also not quite correct.  TDoK is droppable and has much better Percussion mod as well. See following link. <br /><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=18010" title="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=18010" target="akztarg">http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=18010</a> <br /> <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Sat Jun  5 13:35:27 2004 by bdfoster</span></i></p>
